column5: My sister sent me this picture today of a bird wing. She wanted help to ID it, but I couldn't be much assistance. The mottled colouring reminds me of a woodcock, but the size is too large.  One of my books suggests maybe a ptarmigan in summer plumage, but I don't think they are around the Sudbury area.  Any suggestions?
Looks like an owl, possibly a Great horned.
Some kind of owl.  Not a barred or a great grey, but those downy under feathers hint to a silent stalker..
I'd guess a Long Eared Owl by the size and colour.
